      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "> 2/3 may require mining them into blocks directly if the outputs are non-standard to make\r\n\r\n`self.generateblock(node, address, [tx.serialize().hex()])` is already mining the tx-to-be-spent directly into a block.\r\n\r\n2-of-3 shouldn't make any difference vs 1-of-3 or even 1-of-1 afaics. If the tx-to-be-spent is already confirmed, there shouldn't be any problem having a spend of a 20-of-20 checkmultisig in the mempool, so I don't think n/m=4 is actually an edge case. I think a 0-of-0 checkmultisig is also fine to spend, though is non-standard to create.",
